          "text": "If your channel was selected, you have earned Stacc's recognition as one of the 100 best SEO YouTube channels of 2026.\n\nDisplay your award on your site. Email hello@thestacc.com with the subject line \"Best SEO YouTube Channels Badge\" and we will send you a badge image and embed code. Display it on your site or channel page to show your audience you made the list. And link back to this page.\n\n\nThese channels have earned recognition for shaping the foundational principles that every SEO campaign depends on. Subscribe to at least 2 of these for a solid baseline of SEO knowledge.\nAhrefs ,  620K+ subscribers\nNo SEO channel produces more data-driven content than Ahrefs. Sam Oh breaks down keyword research, site audits, and competitive analysis into 10 to 15 minute lessons. Their beginner SEO course has millions of views.\n\nWebsite: ahrefs.com\nYouTube Channel: Ahrefs\nHost: Sam Oh\nX/Twitter: @ahrefs\nLinkedIn: Ahrefs\nBest for: Data-backed SEO fundamentals and keyword research\n\nMoz ,  95K+ subscribers\nMoz built the video series that educated a generation of SEO practitioners. Whiteboard Friday has been a staple of SEO education for over a decade. One expert, one whiteboard, one topic explained clearly. Rotating SEO professionals bring fresh perspectives on on-page SEO and algorithm updates.\n\nWebsite: moz.com\nYouTube Channel: Moz\nHost: Rotating experts\nX/Twitter: @Moz\nLinkedIn: Moz\nBest for: Whiteboard-style explanations of core SEO concepts\n\nSemrush ,  200K+ subscribers\nFew channels match Semrush for the breadth and consistency of SEO education they deliver. They publish tutorials, webinars, and expert interviews covering everything from rank tracking to content gap analysis. Their marketing toolkit walkthroughs help users get value from paid SEO tools.\n\nWebsite: semrush.com\nYouTube Channel: Semrush\nHost: Semrush team\nX/Twitter: @semrush\nLinkedIn: Semrush\nBest for: All-in-one SEO tool walkthroughs and marketing tutorials\n\nGoogle Search Central ,  700K+ subscribers\nThis is the definitive source. The only channel where Google's own engineering team explains how their search engine works. Google publishes updates on algorithm changes, crawling behavior, and structured data straight from the team that builds it. When Google tells you how their search engine works, you listen.\n\nWebsite: developers.google.com/search\nYouTube Channel: Google Search Central\nHost: John Mueller, Gary Illyes, Martin Splitt\nX/Twitter: @googlesearchc\nLinkedIn: Google\nBest for: Official Google guidance on search ranking and indexing\n\nBrian Dean (Backlinko) ,  500K+ subscribers\nBrian Dean created the Skyscraper Technique and turned Backlinko into one of the most trusted SEO brands in the industry. His content focuses on link building and ranking case studies. His library of 100+ videos remains one of the best SEO education collections online.\n\nWebsite: backlinko.com\nYouTube Channel: Backlinko\nHost: Brian Dean\nX/Twitter: @BrianEDean\nLinkedIn: Brian Dean\nBest for: Link building strategy and content-driven SEO\n\nSearch Engine Journal ,  25K+ subscribers\nSearch Engine Journal has earned its place as one of the most trusted voices for SEO news and expert perspective. Their channel features interviews with SEO leaders and industry news recaps, with podcast episodes also appearing as video content. This channel is best for staying current on algorithm updates and industry shifts.\n\nWebsite: searchenginejournal.com\nYouTube Channel: Search Engine Journal\nHost: Rotating SEO experts\nX/Twitter: @sejournal\nLinkedIn: Search Engine Journal\nBest for: SEO news, expert interviews, and industry updates\n\nRand Fishkin (SparkToro) ,  30K+ subscribers\nRand Fishkin is one of the few voices in SEO willing to challenge the consensus with original research and data. The founder of Moz now runs SparkToro, and his channel covers audience research, zero-click searches, and the evolving search market.\n\nWebsite: sparktoro.com\nYouTube Channel: SparkToro\nHost: Rand Fishkin\nX/Twitter: @randfish\nLinkedIn: Rand Fishkin\nBest for: Strategic SEO thinking and audience research\n\nBarry Schwartz (Search Engine Roundtable) ,  15K+ subscribers\nNo one tracks Google search news faster or more reliably than Barry Schwartz. His daily vlogs document algorithm updates, Google bug reports, and search feature changes in real time. He also runs the Search Engine Roundtable blog.\n\nWebsite: seroundtable.com\nYouTube Channel: Search Engine Roundtable\nHost: Barry Schwartz\nX/Twitter: @rustybrick\nLinkedIn: Barry Schwartz\nBest for: Daily Google search news and algorithm update tracking\n\n\nStop writing. Start ranking. Stacc publishes 30 SEO articles per month for your site on autopilot.\nStart for $1 \u2192\n\n\nThese channels have earned recognition for mastering the backend of SEO. The crawl budgets, indexing, site speed, structured data, and JavaScript rendering that most practitioners never fully understand. Pair these with our technical SEO checklist.\nScreaming Frog ,  10K+ subscribers\nScreaming Frog built the most widely used SEO crawling tool in the industry, and their channel is the definitive resource for using it. Every tutorial uses real crawl data to teach log file analysis, broken link detection, and site audits.\n\nWebsite: screamingfrog.co.uk\nYouTube Channel: Screaming Frog\nHost: Screaming Frog team\nX/Twitter: @screamingfrog\nLinkedIn: Screaming Frog\nBest for: Technical site audits and crawl analysis\n\nKoray Tugberk GUBUR ,  25K+ subscribers\nKoray Tugberk GUBUR has become the leading authority on semantic SEO and topical authority. Territory few practitioners dare to enter at this depth. He publishes dense, original case studies on topical maps and content structures aimed at advanced practitioners.\n\nWebsite: holisticseo.digital\nYouTube Channel: Koray Tu\u011fberk G\u00dcB\u00dcR\nHost: Koray Tugberk GUBUR\nX/Twitter: @KorayGubur\nLinkedIn: Koray Tugberk GUBUR\nBest for: Semantic SEO, topical authority, and entity optimization\n\nMartin Splitt (Google). Via Google Search Central\nMartin Splitt is Google's foremost expert on JavaScript SEO, and the clearest voice explaining how Googlebot actually renders the modern web. He explains how Googlebot handles dynamic content and processes single-page applications. His \"SEO Mythbusting\" series is a must-watch.\n\nWebsite: developers.google.com/search\nYouTube Channel: Google Search Central\nHost: Martin Splitt\nX/Twitter: @g33konaut\nLinkedIn: Martin Splitt\nBest for: JavaScript SEO and Google rendering behavior\n\nJohn Mueller (Google). Via Google Search Central\nJohn Mueller is the most accessible Google engineer for the SEO community, consistently providing the clearest official answers on technical questions. He answers technical SEO questions during live office hours and Search Central streams, and his responses are the closest you get to official guidance on crawling and indexing issues.\n\nWebsite: developers.google.com/search\nYouTube Channel: Google Search Central\nHost: John Mueller\nX/Twitter: @JohnMu\nLinkedIn: John Mueller\nBest for: Official Google answers on indexing and crawling\n\nGary Illyes (Google). Via Google Search Central\nGary Illyes offers a rare window into Google Search infrastructure from the engineers who build it. He speaks at conferences about crawl budgets, robots.txt, and Googlebot behavior with a technical depth grounded in engineering realities.\n\nWebsite: developers.google.com/search\nYouTube Channel: Google Search Central\nHost: Gary Illyes\nX/Twitter: @methode\nLinkedIn: Gary Illyes\nBest for: Crawl budget optimization and Googlebot behavior\n\nMike King (iPullRank) ,  15K+ subscribers\nMike King is one of the most cited technical SEO voices at every major industry conference. As CEO of iPullRank, he speaks about information retrieval, log file analysis, and enterprise SEO with an authority that few can match.\n\nWebsite: ipullrank.com\nYouTube Channel: iPullRank\nHost: Mike King\nX/Twitter: @iPullRank\nLinkedIn: Mike King\nBest for: Enterprise technical SEO and information retrieval\n\nLily Ray ,  8K+ subscribers\nLily Ray has established herself as the go-to authority on E-E-A-T and Google core update analysis. As SVP of SEO at Amsive Digital, her analysis of Google core updates is among the most thorough and widely referenced in the industry.\n\nWebsite: lilyray.nyc\nYouTube Channel: Lily Ray\nHost: Lily Ray\nX/Twitter: @lilyraynyc\nLinkedIn: Lily Ray\nBest for: E-E-A-T, core updates, and site quality analysis\n\nCyrus Shepard ,  5K+ subscribers\nCyrus Shepard produces some of the most widely referenced original SEO research published anywhere on the web. The former Moz team member now runs Zyppy, and his research on title tag rewrites and click-through rates is a benchmark for the industry.\n\nWebsite: zyppy.com\nYouTube Channel: Cyrus Shepard\nHost: Cyrus Shepard\nX/Twitter: @CyrusShepard\nLinkedIn: Cyrus Shepard\nBest for: SEO experiments, title tag optimization, and CTR studies\n\n\nThese channels have earned recognition for advancing the craft of link acquisition, outreach, and authority building. Link building remains a core ranking factor. Read our link building strategies guide for the full picture.\nFat Joe ,  5K+ subscribers\nFat Joe is one of the most trusted names in the link building industry, combining a respected service with genuine education. Their channel covers guest posting, niche edits, digital PR, and link prospecting with practical content aimed at agencies and freelancers buying links at scale.\n\nWebsite: fatjoe.com\nYouTube Channel: Fat Joe\nHost: Fat Joe team\nX/Twitter: @fatjoe\nLinkedIn: Fat Joe\nBest for: Link building tactics and outreach at scale\n\nPage One Power ,  3K+ subscribers\nPage One Power has spent 12+ years building a reputation as one of the most credible white-hat link building agencies in the industry. Their channel publishes case studies from real client campaigns covering white-hat link acquisition, content-based outreach, and link audit strategies.\n\nWebsite: pageonepower.com\nYouTube Channel: Page One Power\nHost: Page One Power team\nX/Twitter: @pageonepower\nLinkedIn: Page One Power\nBest for: White-hat link building and content outreach\n\nCharles Floate ,  15K+ subscribers\nCharles Floate is one of the most data-driven experimenters in link building, producing real results from aggressive tactics that others only theorize about. He covers PBN management, tiered link building, and parasite SEO with tests that produce verifiable data.\n\nWebsite: charlesfloate.co.uk\nYouTube Channel: Charles Floate\nHost: Charles Floate\nX/Twitter: @Charles_SEO\nLinkedIn: Charles Floate\nBest for: Advanced link building tactics and PBN strategies\n\nJulian Goldie ,  100K+ subscribers\nJulian Goldie has built one of the highest-output link building channels on YouTube, documenting his own site-building results with full transparency. He covers link building, AI content, and ranking experiments at a publication frequency that sets him apart.\n\nWebsite: juliangoldie.com\nYouTube Channel: Julian Goldie SEO\nHost: Julian Goldie\nX/Twitter: @JulianGoldieSEO\nLinkedIn: Julian Goldie\nBest for: Link building experiments and AI content scaling\n\nRobbie Richards ,  12K+ subscribers\nRobbie Richards created one of the most replicated link building case studies in the industry. A Skyscraper Technique campaign that generated 150K+ organic visits. He focuses on repeatable outreach processes that agencies can scale.\n\nWebsite: robbierichards.com\nYouTube Channel: Robbie Richards\nHost: Robbie Richards\nX/Twitter: @RobbieRich\nLinkedIn: Robbie Richards\nBest for: Outreach-based link building and SEO case studies\n\nJames Dooley ,  20K+ subscribers\nJames Dooley has built a reputation as one of the most results-focused SEO entrepreneurs in the industry, ranking digital real estate that generates measurable returns. He covers link building, expired domains, and authority site creation with a business-first mindset.\n\nWebsite: jamesdooley.com\nYouTube Channel: James Dooley\nHost: James Dooley\nX/Twitter: @JamesDooley_SEO\nLinkedIn: James Dooley\nBest for: Digital real estate, expired domains, and link building\n\nKasra Dash ,  8K+ subscribers\nKasra Dash stands out as a specialist who genuinely understands the intersection of link building and digital PR. He teaches how to earn links through news-based outreach and data-driven content, with strategies built for competitive keywords.\n\nWebsite: kasra.com\nYouTube Channel: Kasra Dash\nHost: Kasra Dash\nX/Twitter: @KasraDash\nLinkedIn: Kasra Dash\nBest for: Digital PR and news-based link acquisition\n\n\nYour SEO team. $99 per month. 30 optimized articles, published automatically to your site.\nStart for $1 \u2192\n\n\nThese channels have earned recognition for their impact on local search. The discipline that determines whether service businesses appear in the map pack. They focus on Google Business Profile, map pack rankings, citations, and local SEO strategy.\nRanking Academy (Luc Durand) ,  270K+ subscribers\nLuc Durand runs the most focused and consistently useful local SEO channel on YouTube. Every video targets small business owners ranking in Google Maps, covering GBP optimization, local citations, and review management with precision.\n\nWebsite: rankingacademy.com\nYouTube Channel: Ranking Academy\nHost: Luc Durand\nX/Twitter: @RankingAcademy\nLinkedIn: Ranking Academy\nBest for: Google Business Profile optimization and local rankings\n\nWhitespark (Darren Shaw) ,  8K+ subscribers\nDo not let the subscriber count fool you. Darren Shaw runs the annual Local Search Ranking Factors Survey. The most cited study in local SEO. Making his channel among the most authoritative in the entire discipline. His tactical guides on citation building and local keyword research are essential.\n\nWebsite: whitespark.ca\nYouTube Channel: Whitespark\nHost: Darren Shaw\nX/Twitter: @DarrenShaw_\nLinkedIn: Darren Shaw\nBest for: Local ranking factors and citation building\n\nChris Palmer SEO ,  40K+ subscribers\nChris Palmer has earned his recognition by managing 200+ client accounts and sharing what actually works from the field. His content covers Google Maps ranking, GBP optimization, and local link building for the real service businesses. Plumbers, dentists, and contractors. That need results.\n\nWebsite: chrispalmermarketing.com\nYouTube Channel: Chris Palmer SEO\nHost: Chris Palmer\nX/Twitter: @ChrisPalmerSEO\nLinkedIn: Chris Palmer\nBest for: Google Maps ranking for service businesses\n\nJoy Hawkins ,  5K+ subscribers\nJoy Hawkins is a Google Business Profile Gold Product Expert. A designation earned by fewer than a handful of practitioners worldwide. Her channel covers GBP bugs, local algorithm updates, and spam fighting tactics with the depth of someone who advises Google on the product itself.\n\nWebsite: sterlingsky.ca\nYouTube Channel: Joy Hawkins\nHost: Joy Hawkins\nX/Twitter: @JoyanneHawkins\nLinkedIn: Joy Hawkins\nBest for: GBP troubleshooting and local algorithm analysis\n\nGreg Gifford ,  5K+ subscribers\nGreg Gifford is one of the most entertaining and insightful voices in local SEO, combining deep tactical knowledge with conference presentations that practitioners actually enjoy watching. As VP of Search at SearchLab Digital, he specializes in local SEO for multi-location businesses.\n\nWebsite: searchlabdigital.com\nYouTube Channel: Greg Gifford\nHost: Greg Gifford\nX/Twitter: @GregGifford\nLinkedIn: Greg Gifford\nBest for: Multi-location local SEO and entertaining presentations\n\nBen Fisher ,  3K+ subscribers\nBen Fisher is a Google Business Profile Platinum Product Expert. An even rarer designation than Gold. Making his expertise on GBP policy essentially unmatched in the public sphere. He helps businesses fix GBP suspensions, manage reviews, and optimize listings.\n\nWebsite: steadydemand.com\nYouTube Channel: Steady Demand\nHost: Ben Fisher\nX/Twitter: @TheSocialDude\nLinkedIn: Ben Fisher\nBest for: GBP suspensions, policy issues, and listing optimization\n\nWes McDowell ,  300K+ subscribers\nWes McDowell has built one of the largest audiences in local service business marketing, trusted by dentists, lawyers, and contractors across the country. He teaches website conversion, local marketing, and SEO for generating leads for service companies.\n\nWebsite: wesmcdowell.com\nYouTube Channel: Wes McDowell\nHost: Wes McDowell\nX/Twitter: @WesMcDowell\nLinkedIn: Wes McDowell\nBest for: Local service business marketing and website conversion\n\n\nThese channels have earned recognition for teaching how to build content-driven websites that generate lasting traffic and revenue. Ideal if you are building a content marketing strategy or scaling a blog.\nAuthority Hacker (Gael Breton and Mark Webster) ,  200K+ subscribers\nAuthority Hacker hosts the number 1 marketing podcast with 3.5 million+ downloads. And their YouTube channel brings that same rigor to authority site building and content scaling. They have built a community of 6,000+ marketing professionals around their methods.\n\nWebsite: authorityhacker.com\nYouTube Channel: Authority Hacker\nHost: Gael Breton, Mark Webster\nX/Twitter: @authorityhacker\nLinkedIn: Authority Hacker\nBest for: Authority site building and affiliate marketing\n\nNiche Pursuits (Spencer Haws) ,  50K+ subscribers\nSpencer Haws has built, grown, and sold multiple niche websites. And documents every step with a transparency that is rare in this industry. His channel covers SEO content writing, affiliate marketing, and keyword strategy with results he is willing to show.\n\nWebsite: nichepursuits.com\nYouTube Channel: Niche Pursuits\nHost: Spencer Haws\nX/Twitter: @nichepursuits\nLinkedIn: Spencer Haws\nBest for: Niche site building and affiliate revenue\n\nIncome School (Ricky Kesler) ,  240K+ subscribers\nIncome School popularized the \"alphabet