d has become one of the most trusted voices for SaaS content strategy, teaching organic growth without paid acquisition in a way that actually scales. His \"Growth Sprints\" framework helps teams prioritize SEO projects with measurable impact.\n\nWebsite: brendanhufford.com\nYouTube Channel: Brendan Hufford\nHost: Brendan Hufford\nX/Twitter: @BrendanHufford\nLinkedIn: Brendan Hufford\nBest for: SaaS content marketing and organic growth strategy\n\nGlen Allsopp (Detailed) ,  5K+ subscribers\nGlen Allsopp publishes research on who actually ranks in Google that has no equivalent anywhere else in the industry. Running Detailed.com, his analysis of search result ownership and media company dominance uncovers patterns that most SEO professionals miss entirely.\n\nWebsite: detailed.com\nYouTube Channel: Glen Allsopp\nHost: Glen Allsopp\nX/Twitter: @ViperChill\nBest for: Search result analysis and ranking pattern research\n\n\n3,500+ blogs published. 92% average SEO score. See what Stacc can do for your site.\nStart for $1 \u2192\n\n\nThese channels have earned recognition for advancing the craft of keyword research and on-page optimization. The fundamentals that determine whether individual pages rank. Read our on-page SEO guide alongside these.\nKyle Roof (Page Optimizer Pro) ,  20K+ subscribers\nKyle Roof earned his place in SEO history by ranking a page about \"rhinoplasty in Plano\" using Lorem Ipsum text. An experiment that proved on-page signals matter more than content quality in some cases and changed how the industry thinks about optimization. He teaches on-page SEO through controlled testing that produces real data.\n\nWebsite: pageoptimizer.pro\nYouTube Channel: Page Optimizer Pro\nHost: Kyle Roof\nX/Twitter: @kyle_roof\nLinkedIn: Kyle Roof\nBest for: On-page SEO testing and page optimization\n\nShelly Fagin ,  3K+ subscribers\nShelly Fagin stands out for delivering practical keyword research and on-page optimization advice that practitioners can implement the same day. She covers real-world client scenarios and actionable fixes with a directness that practitioners value.\n\nWebsite: shellyfagin.com\nYouTube Channel: Shelly Fagin\nHost: Shelly Fagin\nX/Twitter: @ShellyFagin\nLinkedIn: Shelly Fagin\nBest for: Practical keyword research and on-page fixes\n\nSteve Toth ,  8K+ subscribers\nSteve Toth goes deeper into on-page SEO strategy than almost any other channel, pushing well past basic optimization into information gain, content depth, and SERP analysis. His frameworks at SEO Notebook help writers create content that genuinely outranks competitors.\n\nWebsite: seonotebook.com\nYouTube Channel: SEO Notebook\nHost: Steve Toth\nX/Twitter: @SteveTothSEO\nLinkedIn: Steve Toth\nBest for: Advanced on-page strategy and information gain scoring\n\nMordy Oberstein ,  5K+ subscribers\nMordy Oberstein has established himself as one of the sharpest thinkers on SERP analysis and search behavior in the industry. As Head of SEO Brand at Wix, he combines SEO data with search psychology to explain why certain results rank in ways that most practitioners overlook.\n\nWebsite: mordyoberstein.com\nYouTube Channel: Mordy Oberstein\nHost: Mordy Oberstein\nX/Twitter: @MordyOberstein\nLinkedIn: Mordy Oberstein\nBest for: SERP analysis, keyword intent, and search behavior\n\nCrystal Carter ,  3K+ subscribers\nCrystal Carter has earned her recognition as one of the clearest communicators in technical on-page SEO, breaking down complex structured data and SERP features into action items that teams can actually execute. As Head of SEO Communications at Wix, her conference presentations set the standard.\n\nWebsite: crystalcarter.co\nYouTube Channel: Crystal Carter\nHost: Crystal Carter\nX/Twitter: @CrystalCarter\nLinkedIn: Crystal Carter\nBest for: SERP features, structured data, and on-page elements\n\nKevin Indig ,  10K+ subscribers\nKevin Indig brings enterprise-scale SEO thinking to keyword strategy. Shaped by his time as VP of SEO at Shopify. A